This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of job recommendation. It also involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and RNN-based recommendation model, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as sequence modeling, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques such as RNNs also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the modeling of user-item interactions, which is a common problem in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
